
// The code snippet uses the [validators.enum] slot to ensure that the [group_column] argument is one of the specified valid values. It checks if the provided column is among the allowed activity-related columns or the client name, throwing an exception if not. The valid columns include activity_id, client_id, type, date, notes, and client name.
validators.enum:x:@.arguments/*/group_column
   .:activities.activity_id
   .:activities.client_id
   .:activities.type
   .:activities.date
   .:activities.notes
   .:client_id.name
